Plan: Trusted Home Services Platform Implementation
TL;DR: Develop an MVP for a Pakistan-based home services platform using Java (Spring Boot) backend, MySQL database, React Native mobile app, and web dashboard. Focus on user/worker registration, verification, service booking, reviews, emergency dispatch, and payments via JazzCash. Incorporate Google Maps for location services, with no emergency surcharge. This addresses the need for verified, reliable home service workers with fast booking and reviews.

Steps

Project Setup Phase

Create project structure: Backend (Java Spring Boot), Frontend (React Native for mobile, simple web dashboard), Database (MySQL schema).
Set up development environment: Install JDK, Node.js, MySQL, Android/iOS emulators.
Initialize repositories and version control.
Authentication & User Management

Implement user registration for customers and workers: Phone OTP, email verification.
Create user profiles: Name, location, contact for customers; skills, experience, categories for workers.
Depends on step 1
Worker Verification

Add simple verification: Upload CNIC, photo, selfie match.
Assign badges: Verified, Trusted, Emergency Ready based on completion.
Depends on step 2
Service Discovery & Booking

Implement category selection and location-based matching using Google Maps API.
Build booking flow: Select service, time slot, problem description, confirm, payment.
Depends on step 3
Reviews & Ratings

Allow customers to rate (1-5 stars) and review post-service, with optional photos.
Aggregate ratings for workers.
Depends on step 4
Emergency Service

Create emergency booking flow with 30-60 min arrival, real-time tracking via Google Maps.
Dispatch nearest worker without surcharge.
Depends on step 4
Payments Integration

Integrate JazzCash for online payments, implement escrow (hold until confirmation).
Support cash payments with digital receipts.
Depends on step 4
UI/UX & Testing

Design wireframes for booking and emergency flows.
Develop mobile app UI in React Native, web dashboard.
Conduct unit tests, integration tests, and manual QA.
Depends on steps 2-7
Deployment & Scalability

Deploy to cloud (e.g., AWS), start with one city.
Monitor performance, plan for expansion.
Depends on step 8
Relevant files

Backend: src/main/java/com/trustedhome/controller/UserController.java (authentication), WorkerController.java (verification), BookingController.java (booking), PaymentController.java (payments)
Frontend: App.js (React Native main), screens/BookingScreen.js, EmergencyScreen.js
Database: schema.sql (MySQL tables for users, workers, bookings, reviews)
Config: application.properties (database, API keys for Google Maps, JazzCash)
Verification

Run unit tests for backend APIs (e.g., user registration, booking creation).
Test integrations: Google Maps location, JazzCash payment simulation.
Manual testing: End-to-end booking flow on mobile emulator, review submission.
Validate security: Check OTP authentication, data encryption.
Performance check: Simulate concurrent bookings for scalability.
Decisions

Tech stack: Java Spring Boot for backend, React Native for mobile, MySQL for database, based on user preference.
Payments: Include JazzCash, escrow hold, cash option; no Easypaisa unless specified.
Verification: Simple photo/selfie verification, no third-party services.
Location: Google Maps for GPS matching and tracking.
Emergency: No surcharge, focus on fast dispatch.
Scalability: Basic cloud deployment, expand as needed; no specific provider preference.
Language: Support Urdu/English in UI.
Further Considerations

Payment API details: Need JazzCash API documentation for integration.
UI wireframes: Create detailed mockups before coding.
Data privacy: Ensure compliance with Pakistani data laws.
